{
  "answer": "**1. In-Depth User Understanding:** Recognizing the believer's need to comprehend the unseen, the scriptures explicitly command faith in celestial beings as a fundamental pillar of the religion. Surah Al-Baqarah 2:285 directly establishes this by declaring that the Messenger and all the believers have believed in God, His angels, His books, and His messengers [1].\n\n**2. Robust and Enduring Framework:** The physical and operational nature of angels builds a steadfast framework for divine administration. Surah Fatir 35:1 describes this resilient reality by stating that God created the angels as messengers having two, three, or four wings, demonstrating His limitless competence in creation [2].\n\n**3. Elegant and Lucid Presentation:** The Quran elegantly presents the absolute purity and dedication of their existence. The scriptures lucidly explain that the angels exalt God night and day and never slacken in their devotion [3]. Furthermore, they are never arrogant, but rather they constantly fear their Lord and flawlessly execute whatever they are commanded to do [4, 5]. \n\n**4. Seamless and Accessible Experience:** To seamlessly connect the believers with the divine realm, the scriptures clarify the accessible duties of these noble beings. God sends down the angels with the inspiration of His command to guide humanity [6]. Additionally, the angels continually ask God to confer blessings upon the believers in order to bring them out from darknesses into the light [7].",
